    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-09-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-09-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="731"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d731">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Williams</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-09-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 3, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In view of protracted delay in Sanguily case, of disregard of petition preferred
                    by him on suggestion of authorities that it will secure <pb facs="0870" n="776"
                        xml:id="pg_776"/> his release, and of acquittal of Gerardo Portela, jointly
                    accused with him of kidnapping, the Department feels compelled to demand his
                    immediate trial or release.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
